\viewkind4\uc1\trowd\cellx9354\pard\intbl\lang1042\f0\fs20 SLAP lesion typeII (11\f1\'bd\'c3\f0 -1\f1\'bd\'c3\f0 )\fs24                                                                                                                \cell\row
\fs20\trowd\cellx9354\intbl GII anchor : 12\f1\'bd\'c3\f0                                                                                                                                          Under the general anesthesia, the patient was placed on the operating table in the standard lateral decubitus position and rolled back 30\'a1\'c6to provide adequate assess to the anterior shoulder. Skin drapping and preparation were done from finger to right chest area as a usual manner. The arm was placed in a sterile shoulder traction and rotation sleeve. The arm was positioned in approximately 70\'a1\'c6of abduction and 20\'a1\'c6of frontal flexion. Ten pounds of traction was applied. A posterior portal was created 1cm medial and 2 to 3cm caudal to the posterolateral corner of the acromion. The anterior portal was created after the posterior portal by passing the anthroscope, under visual control, superior and anterior to the biceps tendon in the rotator interval. A probe was inserted to anterior and posterior portal, systemic examination of left shoulder joint was performed. Generally, severe degenerative change were observed. There were seen subacromial bursitis and SLAP lesion.  The arthroscope was removed from the posterior cannula and a switching stick was advanced anteriorly through the capsule and into a subcutaneous position lateral and cephalad to the coracoid process. A superficial counter incision was made and a cannula was advanced over the switching stick into the joint in a retrograde fashion. The anterior midglenoid(AMG) portal was created in an outside to inside fashion. A 5mm superficial skin incision was made 2cm inferior to the anterosuperior(AS) portal and 1cm lateral to the coracoid process. An cannula with blunt obturator was then passed through the anterior structure and penetrated the joint. With the arthroscope in the AS portal, a shaver was introduced through the AMG portal and used to initially debride scar tissue, labral, cartilage debris. And SLAP lesion repair with GII anchor. All instrument were removed. Hemovac(200cc) was inserted, and wound was closed. dressing was done.\fs24\cell\row
\intbl\cell\row
\pard\f1\fs20 
