{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0\deflang1033\deflangfe1042{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2\'c3\'bc;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs20   Under the general anesthesia, the patient was placed on the operating table in the standard left lateral decubitus position and rolled back 30\'a1\'c6 to provide adequate assess to the anterior shoulder. The shoulder and arm were then cleansed with an antimicrobial solution and draped. The arm was placed in a sterile foam shoulder traction and rotation sleeve. The arm was positioned in approximately 75\'a1\'c6of abduction and 20\'a1\'c6of frontal flexion. Ten pounds of traction was applied. A posterior portal was created 1cm medial and 3cm caudal to the posterolateral corner of the acromion. 
\par  On arthroscopic finding, we can see full thickness rotator cuff tear in the glenohumeral joint.
\par We switched the arthroscope in the subacromial space. And.we can see  tear of rotator cuff at greater tuberisity, bony spur and bursitis. So we performed subacromial decompression and bursectomy. And we performed rotator cuff repair using anchor screw by double row technics. We confirmed the very firmed rotator cuff after suture.
\par  After debridement was finished, joint irrigation was done. Wound was closed. Compressive dressing was done. And Abduction brace was applied.
\par }

